Rubalcaba to Ask Chacon Not to Run for Leader, Confidencial Says

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-04-04T07:01:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/rubalcaba-to-ask-chacon-not-to-run-for-leader-confidencial-says.html
Spanish Deputy Prime Minister
Alfredo Perez Rubalcaba will ask Defense Minister Carme Chacon
not to run in Socialist party primary elections ahead of the
2012 general election, El Confidencial reported, citing unnamed
people close to Rubalcaba.  In exchange, Rubalcaba will offer Chacon the party
leadership after the 2012 general elections if the Socialists
lose, the online newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net  